  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.5.6\r\nOS & Version: Ubunt 16.04\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWith Geth 1.5.5 in light mode (which I love, thank you!), we could submit contract transactions (mostly minting or deleting our ERC-20 tokens). Just as normal, and they would be mined, and everything would be great.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAfter upgrading to 1.5.6, when a transaction is submitted, a transaction hash is returned, but geth stops syncing and the transaction is never mined. Geth essentially freezes - no more syncing updates in the logs, and the blockNumber is frozen. The transaction stays in the pending pool until geth is restarted, at which point the transaction is lost.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nI have tried several times with different transactions. Have downgraded back to geth 1.5.5 for the time being.\r\n\r\n",
